data.meta_description: Josearmando Diaz (31) Catcher/First Baseman - 2024 SEASON Appeared in 39 games and made 26 starts Recorded 27 hits in 104 at bats, including five doubles Hit...
data.text:
2024 SEASON

Appeared in 39 games and made 26 starts

Recorded 27 hits in 104 at bats, including five doubles

Hit four home runs, drove in 22 runs and walked 22 times

Batted .260, had a .403 on base percentage and a .423 slugging percentage

Had five multi-hit games, including a three-hit performance with two home runs and four RBI’s against Maryland (April 16)

Had 168 putouts and nine assists, leading to a .978 fielding percentage

2023 SEASON

Appeared in 47 games, starting 38, at both catcher and first base, batting .311 with two home runs and 25 RBIs

Walked twice at Ole Miss

Drove in three runs against Charleston

Went 4-for-5 with two RBIs at Northeastern

Went 3-for-5 with a triple and two RBIs at William & Mary

Hit first homer of the season against #21 Maryland

Also clubbed a homer at Monmouth

Went 2-for-3 with a double in the CAA Tournament at Charleston

MERCER COUNTY CC

• 2022 first team All-GSAC and all-region second team

HIGH SCHOOL

• Four-year varsity player at Colegio San Ignacio de Loyola in San Juan, Puerto Rico

PERSONAL

• Son of Ana Mayra Rivera and Jose Alejandro Díaz

• Has a sibling, Alexarmando Diaz, who played at La Salle University (2018) and University of Rhode Island (2020-22) and is now the pitching coach at Lafayette College

• Public relations major at Delaware
